TITLE: Executing YAML Script with TypeScript and YAML
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the runYaml method to execute a YAML script that performs a weather search and query. The script includes AI-assisted actions and queries.
SOURCE: https://github.com/web-infra-dev/midscene/blob/main/apps/site/docs/en/API.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const { result } = await agent.runYaml(`
tasks:
  - name: search weather
    flow:
      - ai: input 'weather today' in input box, click search button
      - sleep: 3000

  - name: query weather
    flow:
      - aiQuery: "the result shows the weather info, {description: string}"
`);
console.log(result);
```

